@DougJBalloon @EladNehorai @LarryMishel @adamdavidson I’ve come to understand that the obvious conflicts that I have working for a small weekly Jewish newspaper apply equally to Big Media. To put it most gently, we are intimately enmeshed in the community we cover. They are our readers and our advertisers and our subjects.

@DougJBalloon @EladNehorai @LarryMishel @adamdavidson We are not going to take the lead in covering abuses at our community’s institutions. And we’re not going to go out of our way to share our personal opinions of the theology of some of our clergy.

@DougJBalloon @EladNehorai @LarryMishel @adamdavidson We’re also going to privilege Jewish readings of the Bible and history over Christian ones. That’s who we are.

@DougJBalloon @EladNehorai @LarryMishel @adamdavidson The Times and the Post and the Atlantic are just the same only the community is sent obvious — because the community is well-off, mostly white, mostly older Americans. It is a community no more eager to accept new ideas than are the rabbis of our local chassidic synagogues.

@DougJBalloon @EladNehorai @LarryMishel @adamdavidson Just as I have to be aware of the possible discomfort of Orthodox readers — my dentist once complained to me about the non-orthodox rabbi who writes for us regularly — MSM has to be aware of discomfitting Republicans, because most well off white men are Republican.

@DougJBalloon @EladNehorai @LarryMishel @adamdavidson That’s why complaints about the Times police stenography don’t register - the complainers may have the receipts, they may live in New York — but they’re not the Times’ community.
